item.title: CVE-2019-18575|2024-09-17T01:25:33.000Z -- dell -- dell%20command%20configure%20%28dcc%29
item.description: Dell Command Configure versions prior to 4.2.1 contain an uncontrolled search path vulnerability. A locally authenticated malicious user could exploit this vulnerability by creating a symlink to a target file, allowing the attacker to overwrite or corrupt a specified file on the system.
